\section{Problem Statement}

Existing KG-constrained decoding frameworks, including GCR and DoG, construct their constraint oracles primarily as functions of the knowledge graph and the question entities, independent of the semantic direction of generation. This design guarantees structural faithfulness, but it does not adapt the valid token set to the question meaning or to the partially generated reasoning chain.

Consequently, current methods conflate structural validity with contextual relevance. They are often too broad, because they admit many structurally valid but semantically irrelevant paths, and too rigid, because they do not narrow sufficiently as generation progresses. In multi-hop settings, where valid path counts grow rapidly with hop depth, this forces the LLM to perform semantic discrimination using parametric knowledge, partially reintroducing the hallucination risk constrained decoding is intended to suppress.

This project addresses the following problem: current KG-constrained decoding frameworks do not condition the valid token constraint on question semantics or generation state, leaving the model responsible for selecting among valid-but-irrelevant paths at each step. The proposed DCA-Trie formulation upgrades the constraint from
\begin{equation}
    W_{\text{val}}(t) = f(G, E_q)
\end{equation}
to
\begin{equation}
    W_{\text{val}}(t) = f(G, E_q, q, y_{<t}),
\end{equation}
so that structural validity and contextual relevance are enforced jointly during decoding.

\section{Aim and Objectives}

This project aims to design, implement, and evaluate a Dynamic Context-Aware Trie (DCA-Trie) framework for KG-constrained LLM generation, where the valid token set at each decoding step is conditioned jointly on graph structure, question semantics, and partial generation, improving multi-hop KGQA accuracy while maintaining structural faithfulness.

To achieve this aim, the following objectives are pursued:

\begin{enumerate}[label=\roman*.]
    \item Characterise the permissiveness problem in existing KG-constrained decoding by defining and measuring the Semantic Irrelevance Ratio (SIR) on WebQSP and CWQ, stratified by hop depth.
    \item Design a semantic relevance scoring mechanism using pretrained sentence-transformer embeddings for filtering candidate KG paths by joint relevance to the question and partial generation.
    \item Implement a static semantic filtering variant (DCA-Trie v1) applied during KG-Trie construction, reducing trie size while keeping false negatives on gold paths below 5\% on validation data.
    \item Implement a step-wise dynamic expansion variant (DCA-Trie v2) that updates constraints after each committed triplet using relevance scoring conditioned on $q$ and $y_{<t}$.
    \item Evaluate DCA-Trie v1 and v2 against GCR and unconstrained CoT baselines on WebQSP and CWQ using Hits@1, F1, structural faithfulness, SIR, and average trie size.
\end{enumerate}

