\subsection{Facilities}

The following facilities were used during project execution:

\begin{enumerate}[label=\roman*.]
    \item University GPU resources and Google Colab Pro for constrained decoding and inference experiments.
    \item University library systems and academic databases for literature review and citation verification.
    \item University internet infrastructure for dataset access and checkpoint retrieval.
    \item Shared GitHub repository infrastructure for version control and reproducibility.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Methods Used}

The project employed the following methods:

\begin{enumerate}[label=\roman*.]
    \item Systematic literature review on constrained decoding, KGQA, retrieval-augmented generation, and LLM hallucination.
    \item Formal gap analysis of GCR, DoG, grammar-constrained decoding, and efficient guided generation methods.
    \item Formal specification of DCA-Trie, including SIR, semantic filtering, and dynamic expansion rules.
    \item Reproduction of the GCR baseline on WebQSP to establish a verified reference implementation.
    \item Implementation of DCA-Trie v1 and v2 as extensions to the baseline inference pipeline.
    \item Quantitative evaluation on WebQSP and CWQ using Hits@1, F1, faithfulness, SIR, and average trie size, with hop-stratified analysis.
    \item Ablation studies on relevance threshold, encoder choice, and beam size.
    \item Qualitative error analysis of false-negative filtering cases and other failure modes.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Scope of Work}

This dissertation develops and evaluates DCA-Trie for multi-hop KGQA on Freebase-grounded benchmarks (WebQSP and CWQ), using GCR's released Llama-based checkpoint and inference-time semantic filtering without additional model fine-tuning.

The work is bounded to the KGQA setting and does not evaluate transfer to other knowledge graphs or non-KG tasks. Production-scale deployment, online latency optimisation, and enterprise-specific graph integration are also outside scope. Faithfulness is assessed empirically through structural validation and answer-path preservation rather than through formal proof of all dynamic-pruning properties.

\section{Organization of Work}

This thesis is organised as follows:

\begin{description}
    \item[Chapter 2] Presents the literature review and identifies the gaps motivating DCA-Trie.
    \item[Chapter 3] Describes the methodology, including formal definitions and system design.
    \item[Chapter 4] Reports experimental results and analysis across WebQSP and CWQ.
    \item[Chapter 5] Concludes the thesis with contributions, limitations, and future directions.
\end{description}
